@page "/get-started"

<h1>Get Started</h1>
<h2>Install</h2>
<p>
    You can add from nuget package to your project in one of the followings ways:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Install using Package Manager Console <var>Install-Package BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended</var></li>
    <li>Install the packege from command line by running <var>dotnet add package BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended</var></li>
    <li>Add reference into the project file <var>&lt;PackageReference Include="BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended" Version="3.5.22" /&gt;</var></li>
    <li>
        Using Visual Nuget Packege Manager
        <hr />
        <img src="images/BlazorBasicsInputFileExtended.JPG" />
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>Import the namespace</h2>
<p>
    Open the <strong>_Imports.razor</strong> file of your Blazor application and add this lines
    <ul>
        <li>
            <var>@@using BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended</var>
        </li>
        <li>
            <var>@@using BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended.Models</var>
        </li>
        <li>
            <var>@@using BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended.ValueObjects</var>
        </li>
        <li>
            <var>@@using BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended.Exceptions</var> only if you will use events OnError
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>

<h2>Use a component</h2>
<p>
    When you need upload a file add this code in the razor view:
    <pre>
<code>
    &lt;InputFileComponent OnChange=LoadFiles /&gt;
@@code{
    void LoadFiles(FilesUploadEventArgs e)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"{e.Count} files to manage");
    }
}
</code>
</pre>
</p>
<ul>
    <li><var>TargetToPostFile</var> is the end point where the form must be send the file.</li>
    <li><var>ButtonShow</var> display the button to upload.</li>
    <li><var>CleanOnSuccessUpload</var> remove the file from the view after upload.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    This code show a button like this:
    <InputFileComponent OnChange=LoadFiles />
</p>

@code {
    void LoadFiles(BlazorBasics.InputFileExtended.Models.FilesUploadEventArgs e)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"{e.Count} files to manage");
    }
}
